<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCFFF868BB465C5FEC0FB33" box="[151,263,1206,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Homalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCFFF868BB465C5FEC0FB33" box="[151,263,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">Homalota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCFFF868A2D65C4FE9EFB32" box="[270,345,1207,1230]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">stigma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCFFF868A4165C5FDCBFB33" author="Erichson" box="[354,524,1206,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" refString="Erichson, W. F. (1839) Genera et species Staphylinorum insectorum coleopterorum familiae. F. H. Morin, Berlin, pp. i - viii, 1 - 400." type="book chapter" year="1839">
Erichson, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868AF665C4FDCBFB33" box="[469,524,1207,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1839.0">1839</number>
</bibRefCitation>
/ labeled by 
<collectionCode id="6B88AE33FFCFFF8689B865C4FCC4FB32" box="[667,771,1207,1230]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">MNHUB</collectionCode>
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86882F65C4FC8EFB33" box="[780,841,1207,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="2013.0">2013</number>
’ [red label, printed in black]. Note 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868FFF65C4FB2BFB33" box="[1244,1260,1207,1231]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1.0">1</number>
: In the original description 
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCFFF868A3F65A9FE15FB0F" author="Erichson" box="[284,466,1242,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" refString="Erichson, W. F. (1839) Genera et species Staphylinorum insectorum coleopterorum familiae. F. H. Morin, Berlin, pp. i - viii, 1 - 400." type="book chapter" year="1839">
Erichson (
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868AB365A8FE0DFB0F" box="[400,458,1243,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1839.0">1839</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
did not specify how many specimens he studied. We received from 
<collectionCode id="6B88AE33FFCFFF868FC365A8FAF6FB0E" box="[1248,1329,1243,1266]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">ZMHB</collectionCode>
only one specimen labelled as 
<typeStatus id="D2228854FFCFFF868AB6658CFE0FFAEB" box="[405,456,1279,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">type</typeStatus>
, here named 
<typeStatus id="D2228854FFCFFF868949658CFD02FAEB" box="[618,709,1279,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">syntype</typeStatus>
. Note 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868834658CFCEFFAEB" box="[791,808,1279,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="2.0">2</number>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCFFF86881A658CFC15FAEB" author="Pace" box="[825,978,1278,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" refString="Pace, R. (1987 b) Revision delle Aleocharinae dell'Argentina sudorientale descritte da Scheerpeltz nel 1972 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 48, 161 - 185." type="journal article" year="1987" yearSuffix="b">
Pace (
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF8688A1658DFC7BFAEB" box="[898,956,1278,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1987.0">1987</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
published the 
<typeStatus id="D2228854FFCFFF868FA6658DFB2BFAEB" box="[1157,1260,1278,1303]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation of 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCFFF868BB46451FE46FAC7" box="[151,385,1314,1339]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCFFF868BB46451FEE9FAC7" box="[151,302,1314,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tricolpochila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tricolpochila</taxonomicName>
stigma
</emphasis>
, however the designation label in the 
<typeStatus id="D2228854FFCFFF8688166450FCA2FAC7" box="[821,869,1315,1339]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">type</typeStatus>
material is missing. Note 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868FB06450FB63FAC7" box="[1171,1188,1315,1339]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="3.0">3</number>
: we received the 
<typeStatus id="D2228854FFCFFF868E4F6450FA5BFAC7" box="[1388,1436,1315,1339]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">type</typeStatus>
material with labels organized in that sequence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4583657DFFCFFF858BE46419FE42FE99" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="228" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" type="description">
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCFFF868BE46419FCC2FA13" blockId="1.[151,1437,954,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCFFF868BE46419FEB3FA7F" bold="true" box="[199,372,1386,1411]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">Redescription.</emphasis>
Female. Maximum body length: 3.0 mm; maximum elytra width: 
<quantity id="CA619B13FFCFFF868F496418FB03FA7E" box="[1130,1220,1387,1411]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
. Body broad; sides subparallel; uniformly light-brown with darker spot on tergite 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86887164FDFCA5FA5B" box="[850,866,1422,1447]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="6.0">6</number>
; dorsal surface glossy; setigerous pores sparse and more densely on head, pronotum and elytra; pronotum with pubescence directed latero-posteriad; elytra and abdomen with pubescence straight and direct posteriad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCFFF868BE46489FB36F8F3" blockId="1.[151,1437,954,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">
Head as long as wide; eyes about as long as temples; infraorbital carina complete. Antennal article 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868E346489FAE3F9EF" box="[1303,1316,1530,1555]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="2.0">2</number>
nd slightly shorter than 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868A05676CFEF7F9CB" box="[294,304,1567,1591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1.0">1</number>
st and longer than 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868929676DFDD0F9CB" box="[522,535,1566,1591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="3.0">3</number>
rd; article 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF8689AD676DFD5BF9CB" box="[654,668,1566,1591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="4.0">4</number>
th subquadrate, articles 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86888F676DFC24F9CB" box="[940,995,1566,1591]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10</number>
transverse and gradually increasing in width toward antennal apex; article 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86891B6731FD94F9A7" box="[568,595,1602,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="10.0">10</number>
th twice as wide as long; article 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF8688F26731FC2DF9A7" box="[977,1002,1602,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="11.0">11</number>
th as long as articles 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868FC66730FADAF9A7" box="[1253,1309,1603,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10</number>
combined. Mandibles broad and curved at apex. Maxila with galea extending slightly beyond apex of lacinia (
<figureCitation id="95A22A73FFCFFF868E276715FA80F983" box="[1284,1351,1638,1663]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[175,1416,928,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[158,1428,913,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Polylobus stigma, female. 1 — right maxilla; 2 — labium; 3 — right tarsus; 4 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868E196714FA80F983" box="[1338,1351,1639,1663]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), galea narrower than lacinia; apical lobe of galea covered with fine and short setae; internal margin of galea with long subapical setae; apical 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868AB967DCFE63F93B" box="[410,420,1711,1735]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868A9367DCFE79F93B" box="[432,446,1711,1735]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="3.0">3</number>
of lacinia with a row of spines, middle portion covered with numerous setae; maxillary palpus with 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868A0167A0FEF7F917" box="[290,304,1747,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="4.0">4</number>
articles, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868ABB67A1FE62F917" box="[408,421,1746,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="2.0">2</number>
nd slightly shorter than 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86899667A1FD05F917" box="[693,706,1746,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="3.0">3</number>
rd, and 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86883967A1FCEFF917" box="[794,808,1746,1771]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="4.0">4</number>
th about half length of thepreceeding one. Labium with ligula split into two lobes (
<figureCitation id="95A22A73FFCFFF868AE06785FDC0F8F3" box="[451,519,1782,1807]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[175,1416,928,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[158,1428,913,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Polylobus stigma, female. 1 — right maxilla; 2 — labium; 3 — right tarsus; 4 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868AD46784FDC0F8F3" box="[503,519,1783,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); labial palpus with 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF8689C86784FD3EF8F3" box="[747,761,1783,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="3.0">3</number>
articles, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86887C6784FCAEF8F3" box="[863,873,1783,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1.0">1</number>
st the longest and 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868F1B6785FB82F8F3" box="[1080,1093,1782,1807]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="2.0">2</number>
nd the shortest.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCFFF868BE46668FA5AF81B" blockId="1.[151,1437,954,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">
Pronotum transverse, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868AE16669FE22F8CF" box="[450,485,1818,1843]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as wide as long, broadest at basal half, anterior margin straight, lateral and posterior margin convex; hypomera invisible in lateral view. Prosternum transverse. Elytra slightly broader than pronotum; 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868A316610FEF2F887" box="[274,309,1891,1915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="1.2">1.2</number>
times as long as pronotum; posterior outer corners deeply emarginated. 
<collectingCountry id="758E7666FFCFFF868F7D6611FB51F887" box="[1118,1174,1890,1915]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings fully developed. Mesoventrite process about half length of mesocoxae, acute and sharp at apex, mesocoxae contiguous, mesocoxal cavities weakly or not margined posteriorly; isthmus almost the same length as mesoventrite process; metaventrite process almost not existent. Tarsal formula 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86895966BDFD4EF81B" box="[634,649,1998,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="5.0">5</number>
- 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF8689B166BDFD66F81B" box="[658,673,1998,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="5.0">5</number>
- 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86898966BDFD7EF81B" box="[682,697,1998,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="5.0">5</number>
; tarsomere 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF86881966BDFC8FF81B" box="[826,840,1998,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="5.0">5</number>
the longest (
<figureCitation id="95A22A73FFCFFF8688F566BDFBDEF81B" box="[982,1049,1998,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[175,1416,928,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[158,1428,913,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Polylobus stigma, female. 1 — right maxilla; 2 — labium; 3 — right tarsus; 4 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225884/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="227">
Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868F2966BCFBDEF81B" box="[1034,1049,1999,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), as long as 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868F8166BDFB69F81B" box="[1186,1198,1998,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="3.0">3</number>
rd and 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCFFF868FDE66BDFACDF81B" box="[1277,1290,1998,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="227" value="4.0">4</number>
th combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCCFF858BB461E4FBB2FEC3" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
Abdomen gradually narrowing apically, first four visible terga deeply impressed basally; segment 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858E2261EBFAC8FF53" box="[1281,1295,152,175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="7.0">7</number>
the longest. Tergite 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858BCF61CFFF3DFF28" box="[236,250,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="8.0">8</number>
sparsely pubescence in posterior half, bearing three prominent setae at each side (
<figureCitation id="95A22A73FFCCFF858FA961CFFB09FF29" box="[1162,1230,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1232,1255]" captionTargetBox="[184,1411,198,1215]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1242]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Polylobus stigma, female. 5 — tergite 8, dorsal view; 6 — sternite 8, ventral view; 7 — tergites 9 – 10, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858F9D61CFFB09FF29" box="[1214,1230,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); posterior margin truncate. Sternite 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858A446193FEB2FF04" box="[359,373,224,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="8.0">8</number>
sparsely pubescence in posterior half, bearing one prominent setae at each side (
<figureCitation id="95A22A73FFCCFF858E6061ACFA4AFF04" box="[1347,1421,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1232,1255]" captionTargetBox="[184,1411,198,1215]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1242]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Polylobus stigma, female. 5 — tergite 8, dorsal view; 6 — sternite 8, ventral view; 7 — tergites 9 – 10, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858E5E61ACFA4AFF04" box="[1405,1421,223,248]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
); posterior margin broadly rounded. Tergite 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF8589596077FD51FEE0" box="[634,662,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="10.0">10</number>
slightly emarginated at apex and fused with tergite 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858FC56077FB33FEE0" box="[1254,1268,260,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="9.0">9</number>
medially (
<figureCitation id="95A22A73FFCCFF858E4C6077FF60FEBC" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1232,1255]" captionTargetBox="[184,1411,198,1215]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,163,1242]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 7. Polylobus stigma, female. 5 — tergite 8, dorsal view; 6 — sternite 8, ventral view; 7 — tergites 9 – 10, dorsal view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858BB4605BFF60FEBC" box="[151,167,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca L-shaped (
<figureCitation id="95A22A73FFCCFF858AE86054FDD6FEBC" box="[459,529,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[175,1416,928,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[158,1428,913,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Polylobus stigma, female. 1 — right maxilla; 2 — labium; 3 — right tarsus; 4 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/225884/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858923605BFDD6FEBC" box="[512,529,296,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); subspherical capsule, with slightly invaginated apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCCFF858BE4603FFE42FE99" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,861]" box="[199,389,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4583657DFFCCFF858BE4601CFB18FCA1" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCCFF858BE4601CFDEBFE2C" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858BE4601CFEA7FE74" bold="true" box="[199,352,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="758E7666FFCCFF858A4B601CFE77FE74" box="[360,432,367,392]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. In the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF8589CD601CFC50FE74" author="Erichson" box="[750,919,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Erichson, W. F. (1839) Genera et species Staphylinorum insectorum coleopterorum familiae. F. H. Morin, Berlin, pp. i - viii, 1 - 400." type="book chapter" year="1839">
Erichson 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF8588786003FC50FE74" box="[859,919,368,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="1839.0">1839</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and on the label of the 
<typeStatus id="D2228854FFCCFF858F8D6003FB19FE74" box="[1198,1246,368,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">type</typeStatus>
material there is not precise information about the locality, only that the material was donated by Germar (
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858FC260E7FA57FE50" author="Erichson" box="[1249,1424,404,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Erichson, W. F. (1839) Genera et species Staphylinorum insectorum coleopterorum familiae. F. H. Morin, Berlin, pp. i - viii, 1 - 400." type="book chapter" year="1839">
Erichson 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858E7760E7FA57FE50" box="[1364,1424,404,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="1839.0">1839</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), presumably Ernst Friedrich Germar.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCCFF858BE460AFFE00FE09" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,861]" box="[199,455,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858BE460AFFE8DFE09" bold="true" box="[199,330,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Bionomics.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCCFF858BE4608CFE7BFD54" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858BE4608CFE49FDE4" bold="true" box="[199,398,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Taxonomic note.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858AB46373FDAEFDE4" author="Pace" box="[407,617,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Pace, R. (1987 b) Revision delle Aleocharinae dell'Argentina sudorientale descritte da Scheerpeltz nel 1972 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 48, 161 - 185." type="journal article" year="1987" yearSuffix="b">
Pace (
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858AFD608CFDDDFDE4" box="[478,538,511,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="1987.0">1987</number>
b: 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF8589156373FDA6FDE4" box="[566,609,512,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="170.0">170</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF8589C8608CFC68FDE4" box="[747,943,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF8589C8608CFC9CFDE4" box="[747,859,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Polylobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Polylobus</taxonomicName>
stigma
</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF8588D7608CFF1DFDC0" authority="Scheerpeltz, 1972" authorityName="Scheerpeltz" authorityYear="1972" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tricolpochila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="topaliana">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF8588D7608CFAC7FDE4" box="[1012,1280,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Tricolpochila topaliana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858E32608CFF14FDC0" author="Scheerpeltz" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Scheerpeltz, O. (1972) Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Studienreise von Gy. Topal nach Sudwest-Argentien (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Folia Entomologica Hungarica, 25 (Supplement), 1 - 268, pls. 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1972">
Scheerpeltz, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858BB46357FF14FDC0" box="[151,211,548,572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and in 
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858A176356FDEAFDC0" author="Pace" box="[308,557,548,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Pace, R. (2000) Aleocharinae del Cile, nuove o poco note (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) (157 º Contributo alla conoscenza delle Aleocharinae). Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino, 17, 355 - 510." type="journal article" year="2000">
Pace (
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858A5A6357FE71FDC0" box="[377,438,548,572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="2000.0">2000</number>
: 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858AE26357FDE2FDC0" box="[449,549,548,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="496498.0">496, 498</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF8589886356FCC8FDC0" box="[683,783,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">P. s t i gm a</emphasis>
with 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF8588716356FB54FDC0" authority="Pace, 2000" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="2000" box="[850,1171,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Polylobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valparaisensis">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF8588716356FBD7FDC1" box="[850,1040,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">P. valparaisensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858F3B6356FB54FDC0" author="Pace" box="[1048,1171,548,572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Pace, R. (2000) Aleocharinae del Cile, nuove o poco note (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) (157 º Contributo alla conoscenza delle Aleocharinae). Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino, 17, 355 - 510." type="journal article" year="2000">
Pace, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858F786357FB54FDC0" box="[1115,1171,548,572]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858FE86356FF15FD9C" authority="Pace, 2000" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Polylobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulifer">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858FE86356FA9FFDC1" box="[1227,1368,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">P. granulifer</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858E436356FF15FD9C" author="Pace" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Pace, R. (2000) Aleocharinae del Cile, nuove o poco note (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) (157 º Contributo alla conoscenza delle Aleocharinae). Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino, 17, 355 - 510." type="journal article" year="2000">
Pace, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858BB4633BFF15FD9C" box="[151,210,584,608]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, respectively. According to Pace, the characters easily separate 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF8588E3633AFBE0FD9C" box="[960,1063,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">P. s t i g m a</emphasis>
from them are: length of eyes, punctures on elytra and general form of spermatheca. Unfortunately, in this work it was not possible to compare 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858EA4631EFF25FD54" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">P. stigma</emphasis>
with those species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D2636F6FFCCFF858BE463C7FB18FCA1" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
Following 
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858A6163C7FD5BFD30" author="Klimaszewski" box="[322,668,692,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Klimaszewski, J. &amp; Sturm, H. (1991) Four new especiess of the Oxypodine genus Polylobus Solier (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) collected on the flower heads of some high Andean giant rosette plants (Espeletiinae: Asteraceae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 45, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1991">
Klimaszewski &amp; Sturm (
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF85897963C7FD53FD30" box="[602,660,692,716]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
the genus have galea with sponge-like apical bristles, not seen in 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858EA463C6FF25FD0C" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">P. stigma</emphasis>
. The galea of 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858AA163AAFE2FFD0C" box="[386,488,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">P. stigma</emphasis>
has internal margin with long subapical setae, very similar to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858E1D63A4FA5CFD0C" box="[1342,1435,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stethusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858E1D63A4FA5CFD0C" box="[1342,1435,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Stethusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858BBD638FFF3AFCE9" box="[158,253,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Athetini">Athetini</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858A34638FFDE5FCE8" author="Gusarov" box="[279,546,764,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Gusarov, V. I. (2002) A revision of Nearctic species of the genus Geostiba Thomson, 1858 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Zootaxa, 81, 1 - 88." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Gusarov 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858AA1638FFE7AFCE8" box="[386,445,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="2002.0">2002</number>
, Fig. 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858920638FFDE5FCE8" box="[515,546,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="12.0">12</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). We also agree with 
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF858800638EFC2DFCE8" author="Pace" box="[803,1002,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Pace, R. (2000) Aleocharinae del Cile, nuove o poco note (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) (157 º Contributo alla conoscenza delle Aleocharinae). Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino, 17, 355 - 510." type="journal article" year="2000">
Pace (
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858848638FFC6FFCE8" box="[875,936,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="2000.0">2000</number>
: 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858895638FFC25FCE8" box="[950,994,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="400.0">400</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
that 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858F0B638FFB5FFCE9" box="[1064,1176,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Polylobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858F0B638FFB5FFCE9" box="[1064,1176,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Polylobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is forming a complex group, at least with 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858AA8626CFD29FCC4" authority="Bernhauer, 1908" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1908" box="[395,750,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Tricolpochila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858AA8626CFDE5FCC4" box="[395,546,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Tricolpochila</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF85890C626CFD29FCC4" author="Bernhauer" box="[559,750,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1908) Beitrag zur Staphylinidenfauna von Sudamerika. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 74, 283 - 372." type="journal article" year="1908">
Bernhauer, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF8589956253FD29FCC4" box="[694,750,800,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858813626CFB43FCC4" authority="Bernhauer, 1908" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1908" box="[816,1156,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Polylobinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858813626CFC71FCC4" box="[816,950,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Polylobinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="69084B07FFCCFF8588E1626CFB43FCC4" author="Bernhauer" box="[962,1156,799,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1908) Beitrag zur Staphylinidenfauna von Sudamerika. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 74, 283 - 372." type="journal article" year="1908">
Bernhauer, 
<number id="BB5124D1FFCCFF858F6A6253FB43FCC4" box="[1097,1156,800,824]" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. We tentatively include 
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858BB46237FE9EFCA0" box="[151,345,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858BB46237FEC0FCA1" box="[151,263,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Polylobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Polylobus</taxonomicName>
stigma
</emphasis>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="CA994D75FFCCFF858ACD6237FD99FCA1" box="[494,606,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Polylobus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3FEDEAE4FFCCFF858ACD6237FD99FCA1" box="[494,606,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="228">Polylobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pending further revision of the genus and related genera.
</paragraph>
